SIMPLE: coadjutor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coadjutor
<hw>Co`ad*ju"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Co</er>-, and <er>Aid</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who aids
another; an assistant; a coworker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Craftily outwitting her perjured <qex>coadjutor</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sheridan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>The assistant of a bishop or
of a priest holding a benefice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coadjutorship</ent>⟦br⟧
